Worried brides-to-be in Lagos have expressed disappointment over the extension of the lockdown of the state by the federal government. President Muhammadu Buhari had in a national broadcast on Monday night announced the extension of lockdown of Abuja, Lagos and Ogun States for another 14 days in an effort to reduce the spread of coronavirus. The president had earlier ordered the lockdown of the states for an initial 14 days that started on March 30 while the extension began on Monday night. In separate interviews with the News Agency Of Nigeria (NAN), the brides-in- waiting said that they were confused and frustrated by the lockdown extension as they had to cancel or further postpone their wedding ceremonies. Miss Abimbola Ajisafe, a childcare giver, said that she had postponed her wedding ceremony when the initial lockdown was imposed on March 30. ”I was hopeful that it would be lifted after 14 days, but it did not happened that way. Having your money tied down indefinitely on wedding plans is no joke,” she said. A lawyer, Miss Sandra Omeche, said that she stopped making further wedding plans when she suspected that the lockdown would be extended. ” My wedding date was fixed for May 2;  so I had been calling my vendors to make sure that they still had certain things in place, but the lockdown extension would hinder certain things. “Just yesterday, my parents decided to postpone the wedding ceremony indefinitely,” Omeche said. Another bride to-be, Miss Simisola Tometi, said that her wedding was slated for  April 18, but the lockdown distorted the plan and left her confused. “I must say that this year has been pretty hard on me and my fiance because it was with great difficulty that we got both families to agree to our union. Just when we thought everything was moving smoothly, the lockdown started,” she lamented. Miss Yetunde Alaka also said that the lockdown hindered her wedding slated for April 5, but was a blessing in disguise as she got to know her fiance’s true marital status because of the lockdown. “I had to stay with my in-laws to-be because of the lockdown and was surprised to hear them discussing about his first wife that I never knew existed. They still don’t know that I know. I just came up with some excuses to go and stay with a family friend residing near them,” she said.